Aim
To discover vulnerable hosts in a network using Metasploit and Nmap integration.
Introduction
Metasploit Framework integrates with Nmap to perform host discovery, service detection, and vulnerability
assessment. The scan results are stored in the Metasploit database for further exploitation and analysis.
Procedure
Step 1: Install PostgreSQL
sudo apt install postgresql -y
Step 2: Install Metasploit Framework
sudo apt install metasploit-framework -y
Step 3: Start PostgreSQL Service
sudo systemctl start postgresql
Step 4: Initialize Database
sudo msfdb init
Step 5: Open Metasploit Console
msfconsole
Step 6: Verify Database Connection
db_status
Step 7: Perform Nmap Scan
db_nmap scanme.nmap.org
Step 8: View Hosts and Services
hosts
services
Output
Hosts discovered
Open ports detected
Services identified
Result
Thus, vulnerable hosts were discovered successfully using Metasploit and Nmap integration.
